In terms of language, we could also think this as a federated network of energy, in comparison to a centralized network (national grid) or a decentralized network (microgrids).  We shouldn't lionize federated topologies (nor should we centralized or decentralized topologies) — rather, we should evaluate them on their merits in a given context.  
