Perhaps the problem is the design paradigm of the microgrid.  Trying to distribute the electricicty across all of the different homes, and coordinating that wider network, is where the problems arise. Compare that to creating a renewable installation at a centralized location/hub, and the people coming to that hub for electricity usage?

The latter federated design (each neighborhood having a central installation) seems to be working quite well with battery banks in (), and solar powered community centers in Puerto Rico.

